cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel adaptive guidance system developed using reinforcement meta-learning with a recurrent policy and value function approximator. The paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as reinforcement learning (RL) and neural networks, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also deals with robotics and control systems, which are associated with the cs.RO sub-category. The use of recurrent network layers allows the deployed policy to adapt in real time to environmental forces acting on the agent, which is associated with the cs.LG sub-category. The paper also involves the integration of guidance and navigation, which is associated with the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the optimization of policies using meta-learning, which is associated with the cs.NE sub-category.
